msContents.summary:
A composite paper manuscript, containing four sections: the Pāṇinīya Dhātupāṭha; the Saṃkatāpada, original verses to Saṃkatā composed by the scribe;
                                the Uṇādisūtra in the pañcapadī recension; 
                                and an unidentified fragment in a different hand, written on the final fly leaf.
